# Skill: Async/Event Handler (Frontend)

## Goal
Implement safe async handlers (form submit, button action, effect-triggered load) in feature modules.

## Placement
- Feature hooks: `src/features/<feature>/hooks/`
- Page-local handlers: `src/features/<feature>/pages/*.tsx`
- Shared async helper usage: `src/common/hooks/useAsyncAction.ts`

## Rules
- Validate payload before calling service functions.
- Keep loading/error/success state explicit.
- Keep handler logic in features; do not move to route files.
- Use service layer for API calls; do not call axios directly in components.

## Retry/Idempotency Note
- This project has no backend event bus patterns. Do not introduce queue/event frameworks here.
- For retriable UI actions, implement explicit user-triggered retry in feature UI/state.

## Checklist
- [ ] Handler placed in feature folder
- [ ] Uses existing async helper pattern
- [ ] Handles loading + error + success
- [ ] Calls services, not raw HTTP client
